metadata.name: "Might delete" (CryptoPunk color study)
metadata.description:
On April 1, 2022 Piv tweeted "Who wore it better? Scrambled Phunk pixels vs. 4900 Colours": https://twitter.com/piv_piv/status/1509816169208946689


'Scrambled Phunk pixels' was a pixel art color scramble and I wanted to "do it big" by taking it to millions of pixels of CryptoPunk colors.


The goal was a noise-like effect, but there was a bug in my code that created stripes instead. I thought it looked cool, so I created a version with "light colors only" and Tweeted it with the message "might delete."


The message refers to the fact that the design wasn't "intentional" or "artistic" but rather just looked cool. I don't consider this "art," but it does feel good to look at.


(Of course Gerhard Richter has done stripes as well.)
